	abstract = {Abstract
            
              Objective
              
                17q12 microdeletions containing
                HNF1B
                and intragenic variants within this gene are associated with variable developmental, endocrine, and renal anomalies, often already noted prenatally as hyperechogenic/cystic kidneys. Here, we describe prenatal and postnatal phenotypes of seven individuals with
                HNF1B
                aberrations and compare their clinical and genetic data to those of previous studies.
              
            
            
              Methods
              
                Prenatal sequencing and postnatal chromosomal microarray analysis were performed in seven individuals with renal and/or neurodevelopmental phenotypes. We evaluated
                HNF1B
