	abstract = {Biallelic variants in the
              AEBP1
              gene cause a novel autosomal‐recessive connective tissue disorder (CTD) reminiscent of Ehlers‐Danlos Syndrome (EDS). The four previously reported individuals show considerable clinical variability. Unbiased high‐throughput sequencing enables the rapid identification of additional cases for such rare entities. We identified the homozygous nonsense variant c.917dup, p.Tyr306* in
